com.opengamma.strata.market.curve

Class CurveGroupDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opengamma.strata.market.curve.CurveGroupDefinition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Bean, ImmutableBean

    public final class CurveGroupDefinition
extends Object
implements ImmutableBean, Serializable
    Provides the definition of how to calibrate a group of curves.

    A curve group contains one or more entries, each of which contains the definition of a curve and a set of market data keys specifying how the curve is to be used.

    A curve can be used for multiple purposes and therefore the curve itself contains no information about how it is used.

    In the simple case a curve is only used for a single purpose. For example, if a curve is used for discounting it will be associated with one key of type DiscountCurveKey.

    A single curve can also be used as both a discounting curve and a forward curve. In that case its key set would contain a DiscountCurveKey and a RateIndexCurveKey.

    Every curve must be associated with at least once key.
